1. OS: It acts as a interface between hardware and software
eg are windows(by microsoft), linux, macOS(for apple pc), Android(By Google), iOS (OS for iphones).

2. Program: it is set of instructions written in any programming language
Process: instance of program in execution. (ek part of program in execution) (program have multiple process).
          each process have their own PCB(process control block).
thread: unit of execution within a process.

3. Multiprogramming:
 Multiprogramming means multiple programs are kept in the main memory at the same time, 
and the CPU switches between them so that it is never idle. Example: Excel and Chrome loaded in memory together.

Multiprocessing:
 Multiprocessing means a computer system uses more than one CPU (or processor cores) to execute multiple processes simultaneously.

Multitasking:
 Multitasking means a single CPU performs multiple tasks by rapidly switching between them, giving the illusion that tasks are running at the same time.

